definition.value: A cationic sphingoid that is the conjugate acid of tetradecasphingosine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino function; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of tetradecaphytosphingosine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino function; major species at pH 7.3.
A ceramide consisting of tetradecaphytosphinganine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.
A dihydroceramide consisting of an hexadecasphinganine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of any 2'-O-methylnucleotide 5'-phosphate residue; major species at 7.3.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of any nucleotide 5'-phosphate residue; major species at 7.3.
A ceramide consisting of an hexadecasphing-4-enine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.
A ceramide consisting of an hexadecaphytosphingosine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.
An organic nitrate salt prepared from equimolar amounts of (R)-miconazole and nitric acid.
An organic nitrate salt prepared from equimolar amounts of (S)-miconazole and nitric acid.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecasphingosine.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates glucocorticoid receptors.
A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-yl)ethanol in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a 2,4-dichlorobenzyl group.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecaphytosphingosine.
A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorobenzyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]imidazole that has R configuration.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecasphingosine.
A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorobenzyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]imidazole that has S) configuration.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecaphytosphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as 15-methylhexadecasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as icosasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as icosasphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as icosaphytosphingosine.
A long-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-aminophenylglyoxylic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

A ceramide phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phospho to the amino group of any N-acylhexadecasphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phospho to the amino group of any N-acylicosasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phospho to the amino group of any N-acylicosaphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phospho to the amino group of any N-acyltetradecasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic sulfate of thymol.
A glycine derivative that is the carboxamide obtained by the formal condensation of the amino group of glycine with 2-furoic acid.
A L-tyrosine derivative that is the 3-methoxy derivative of L-dopa.

A ceramide phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phospho to the amino group of any N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-(1H-indol-3-yl)propanoic acid.
A cerebroside in which the sugar head group is a hexose with unspecified stereochemistry attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acylsphingosine.
A cerebroside in which the sugar head group is a hexose with unspecified stereochemistry attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acylsphinganine.
A hexosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the hexosyl component is specified as  beta-D-glucosyl.
